title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1991-09-14
lineage: MAC > Sony WM-D6 > Edirol R09 HR > 24/48 wav > Adobe Audition > Wavelab 6 (with iZotope Ozone 4) > iZotope RX Advanced > 16/44.1 wav > CD Wave > TLH > Flac 16; taped and transferred by John Bleich
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll, Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Little Red Rooster, Jack A Roe, Desolation Row, Tennessee Jed, Promised Land

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Ship of Fools-> Truckin'-> Jam-> Spoonful-> He's Gone, Drums-> Jam-> All Along The Watchtower, China Doll-> One More Saturday Night, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text: Good song selection Of the five or so Archive audience tapes for 9/14/91, this is the best quality version.  Nice song selection, including the lesser-played Jack-A-Roe, Ship of Fools, Spoonful, and China Doll.
